27/5/98: idea for making marbled boxes & buttons:
- create a reasonably large BrickCell, and construct a continuous ByteMap
from it, by setting b(x,y) <- (b(x,y)*x + (wid-x)*b(wid+x,y))/wid,
and sim. in the y-direction.
- create WxH sized TImages in all required colours from this ByteMap,
but don't throw away the ByteMap.
- create Wx2 and 2xH sized TImages to be filled later.
- when drawing a box, tile using the WxH image, then do the edges by
copying the relevant pieces of the ByteMap into the Wx2 and 2xH sized
TImages w/ the proper colours. Use the result to tile the edges.

